.TH "mempool_init" 9 "mempool_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mempool_init \- initialize a memory pool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mempool_init
.BI "(mempool_t *pool "  ","
.BI "int min_nr "  ","
.BI "mempool_alloc_t *alloc_fn "  ","
.BI "mempool_free_t *free_fn "  ","
.BI "void *pool_data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pool" 12
pointer to the memory pool that should be initialized
.IP "min_nr" 12
the minimum number of elements guaranteed to be
allocated for this pool.
.IP "alloc_fn" 12
user-defined element-allocation function.
.IP "free_fn" 12
user-defined element-freeing function.
.IP "pool_data" 12
optional private data available to the user-defined functions.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Like \fBmempool_create\fP, but initializes the pool in (i.e. embedded in another
structure).
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative error code otherwise.
